President Biden has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to serve in key roles on the Board of Visitors to the U.S. Air Force Academy and the Board of Visitors to the U.S. Military Academy. These boards provide independent advice and recommendations on various matters related to the respective academies. The individuals being appointed have diverse backgrounds and experience in areas such as national security, military service, education, and leadership. Some notable appointees include Jenna Hoffman Ben-Yehuda, President and CEO of the Truman Center for National Policy; Eric Kenneth Fanning, President and CEO of the Aerospace Industries Association; and Lieutenant Colonel Roderick Alvendia, a U.S. Army JAG Corps officer. These appointments reflect the administration's commitment to ensuring the academies have strong leadership and oversight.